org.jinq.jpa

Interface JPAJinqStream<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, java.util.stream.BaseStream<T,java.util.stream.Stream<T>>, JinqStream<T>, java.util.stream.Stream<T>

    public interface JPAJinqStream<T>
extends JinqStream<T>
    An extension of the JinqStream that includes support for JPQL specific features like JOIN FETCH

    • Method Detail

      • joinFetch

        <U> JPAJinqStream<T> joinFetch(JinqStream.Join<T,U> join)
        When executing the query, the items referred to be the plural association will be fetched as well. The stream itself will still return the same elements though. 
          JinqStream<Country> stream = ...;
 JinqStream<Country> result = 
    stream.joinFetch(c -> JinqStream.from(c.getCities()));
        Parameters:
        join - function applied to the elements of the stream. When passed an element from the stream, the function should return a stream of values that should be fetched as well
